			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">So, we have our regular, stable summon pets, right?  They aren't the strongest elementals from the planes, but aren't strong enough to break away from being bent under our will.
<br />

<br />
Now, I'm sure that there are stronger elementals sitting in the planes, tooling around, doing their elemental type stuff from day to day.  So, here's what I was thinking.  Doubt it'll be implemented, but wanted to toss the idea in anyway.
<br />

<br />
Change the Call of the Arch Mage spell.  IT no longer charms a summoned mob already in the game.  What it does instead is summons one of these volatile elementals.  Think along the lines of the "Gate" spell from D&D.
<br />

<br />
The monster would stay in the world for a set duration (Say, 3 minutes or until killed).  It would still have a chance to break "charm" during these three minutes.  If it did, it would then decide (random choice) to either attack the mage and his party (a la a charmed mob) or to just go home.  Something like a 20% attack, 80% go home breakdown.
<br />

<br />
This gives mages a chance to have a FAR better pet in certain situations (much like enchanters with charm), along with the risk.
<br />

<br />
Hope to see this in a future game maybe <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Falaanla Marr
<br />
Level 65 Magician
<br />
Luclin</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
