<br />
I'm with Silverblade, but I'd say can the "can turn on you" aspect of it.  Just make it something that is short-lived, but extreme damage, considering our nukes don't necessarily fill that role.  =(
<br />

<br />
Right now after initial casting, in many situations our pets are mana-less damage.  They require occasional re-buffing, but essentially mana-less damage in raid or group situations.  Yes the occasional heals, but in many situations, mana-less.  Make something like this the "mana-pet" where they would have maybe a 1-2 minute duration, but is like a 300-500 hitter (or more), but is gone, and requires another 500+ mana to summon another one.  Or even more mana.  How about 1k mana for a lot of damage?  If it was a lvl 65+, and a 500 hitter, 1.5k might even be balanced if it wasn't easily killed (have it's proc be like MSIV).
<br />

<br />
But I'm against the "it's loose!" idea.  I think that isn't a good idea IMO.  Limited-duration, and high mana cost is enough.<br />_________________<br />Eriol Telcontar
